contents.desc: Today is the anniversary of my dad‚Äôs accident. The day that changed my life forever. I was 10 years old, and the impossible happened. My dad, Superman, was killed in a car accident by a drunk driver. I look back at that night and replay it in my head, and it breaks my heart all over again. I can still remember it like it was yesterday. It took me a long, long time to come to a place where I could find any sort of healing. Of course, as long as we‚Äôre in these imperfect bodies in this fallen world, pain is just something we have to get used to. Today will always be a day associated with sadness for me. With that said, there is also a certain beauty and hope to our tragedies. I see the way God used it for so much good in my life and in the lives of some of those around me. I see how He used it to make me a better man, husband and father (I still have a very long way to go). He doesn‚Äôt waste anything, I can attest to that. I also know and believe that I will get to hug my dad again, and talk to him, and share laughs with him. I believe he WILL get to meet my wife and my 3 beautiful sons, one of whom looks just like him. I believe that with all my heart. So while I can‚Äôt escape the sadness, I choose to cling to those truths and the comfort that my dad knew Jesus and he‚Äôs with Him now. This song, was a gift from God to help heal me, and maybe even help heal one of you. Thank you to @America‚Äôs Got Talent for giving me a stage to share it with the world. Dad, I love you and I miss you. I‚Äôm gonna keep fighting to keep your memory alive through this song and through the stories I share about you with the boys. #Son #originalmusic #truestory
